programme.title: 6 Species in One Episode – Ultimate South African Safari!
programme.desc: In this action-packed continuation of Episode 9, we return to the rugged beauty of Kudu Safaris Africa in the Northern Cape of South Africa for more unforgettable hunting moments with the Huntech Pro team. Larry Stover set out in search of a Zebra, but plans changed quickly when a stunning Yellow Blesbuck crossed his path — a rare colour variant that was too good to pass up. Meanwhile, Dennis Stover had his sights set on a Nyala, and at first light the next morning, the team located a magnificent bull and set off on a thrilling stalk. Host Johan Smit had two species on his list — a Red Lechwe and a Tsessebe. He was the only one in the group yet to take a Lechwe, and when the opportunity finally came, he didn't hesitate. The next day, Johan's dream of hunting a Tsessebe became a reality with a clean front shot at 200 yards. Co-host Beulah Smit had a majestic Sable bull in her sights. When the team found the herd, they carefully closed the distance to line up the perfect shot on a truly special bull. We close out this unforgettable trip with a Dangerous Game hunt as Lance Stover finally gets the chance to pursue his dream animal — the Cape Buffalo. When his uncle gave him the green light, the excitement was written all over his face. Join us as we wrap up an incredible adventure in the Northern Cape — from colour variants and plains game to one of Africa's Big Five. This is one for the books!

programme.title: Moments Made: Annual Hunt with Huntech Pro
programme.desc:
Join us for another unforgettable adventure in Season 5 Episode 10 of Huntech Pro, as we host our Annual Hunt — this year at the stunning Dewou Lodge in the Waterberg!
The action kicks off with Lyril Haneman, who sets her sights on a beautiful Impala ram. With Co-Host Beulah Smit behind the camera, every moment is flawlessly captured. But Lyril wasn't done yet — while waiting patiently in a blind, a majestic Nyala bull appeared, presenting another incredible opportunity. Using the Ravin R26 Crossbow and Thorn Broadheads Crown 100gr, Lyril makes her mark again with precision and grace.
Next up, Matt Kouns teams up with host Johan Smit for a classic spot-and-stalk hunt after Blesbuck. Johan carefully guides Matt into position, where Matt makes a perfect shot with his Tikka UPR 6.5 Creedmoor.
The following day, Johan joins Matt and Corra Shields in a blind as Matt takes on the challenge of hunting Zebra — another unforgettable moment in the episode.
To close it off, Daniel Metsopulos heads out with PH Johnathan Rademeyer to a blind, where they patiently wait for a Waterbuck bull. Their persistence pays off, ending this episode on a high note.
This is an epic bowhunting episode you don't want to miss — packed with adrenaline, skill, and breathtaking wildlife encounters!
And the adventure isn't over yet… We'll continue the action in the next episode as more hunters take on the African bushveld.
Watch now and be part of the Huntech Pro experience!

programme.title: First Blood, Forever Changed with Huntech Pro!
programme.desc: In Episode 11 of Season 5, we continue our annual hunting adventure at the iconic Dewou Lodge with Huntech Pro. The action kicks off with Joe Willis on the trail of a special Blue Wildebeest bull. But as often happens in the bushveld, plans change in a heartbeat—when a magnificent Impala ram stepped out, the team shifted focus for an unexpected opportunity. This episode's emotional highlight belongs to Kelsey Rizzo. She arrived on the trip as a non-hunter, but everything changed after meeting Johan and Beulah Smit. Witnessing their passion for ethical hunting and conservation sparked something in her. With guidance from Johan, Kelsey trained with the Ravin Crossbow and his trusted .308 rifle—quickly showing skill and confidence on the range. Later that afternoon, our PH Jacques Barnard located a herd of Blesbuck, and the stalk was on. What followed was a powerful moment that marked Kelsey's first hunt—an unforgettable milestone that viewers won't want to miss. Meanwhile, PH Johnathan Rademeyer and client Daniel Metsopulos set out in search of a prized White-Flanked Impala ram, showcasing the challenge and patience required to track such a sought-after trophy. To cap off the day, our guests were treated to a surprise performance by traditional South African gumboot dancers—a lively cultural celebration around the evening fire. Finally, Lyril Haneman closes the episode with a meaningful conservation hunt, taking an old Eland cow—a key part of responsible wildlife management. This episode is packed with firsts, unforgettable memories, and the heart of what Huntech Pro is all about. Don't miss it!
